4. PRIVACY, TELEMETRY, AND ADVERTISING RESTRICTIONS
4.1. Prohibited Telemetry: The software or any derivative work SHALL NOT collect, 
transmit, or store any personal data, device identifiers, usage metrics, or behavioral 
analytics unless explicitly requested and manually approved by the end-user (Opt-In). 
Automated, silent, or background transmission of user data is strictly forbidden.
4.2. Necessary Exceptions: Technical data strictly required for the operational 
stability of the software—limited to crash logs, error reports, and critical security 
updates—is permitted, provided that:
  a) It contains zero personally identifiable information (PII).
  b) It is transmitted in plaintext or clearly auditable formats.
  c) The user retains the ability to disable this collection entirely at any time.
4.3. Prohibited Advertising (Adware): The integration of third-party advertising 
networks, dynamic ad-serving components, tracking pixels, or intrusive monetization 
mechanisms that disrupt the core user experience (such as unclosable pop-ups or 
full-screen overlays) is strictly prohibited. Non-compliance immediately revokes rights.

